<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-02T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.4215 Air Pollution/83: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-02T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                        1928—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:35
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>167. Your 103, August 1, 6 p.m. Under Secretary of State for External
                            Affairs informally states the matter will be at once referred to the
                            Prime Minister and considers that there is no doubt of immediate
                            reference in the form proposed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>